    "summary": "Innovative Product Owner and DevOps/SRE engineer with over 5+ years in the government and telecommunications sector. I help organisations like KPN and DUO to create secure, reliable and automated cloud platforms. \n\n\ud835\udde7\ud835\uddf2\ud835\uddf0\ud835\uddf5\ud835\uddfb\ud835\uddf6\ud835\uddf0\ud835\uddee\ud835\uddf9 \ud835\udde6\ud835\uddf8\ud835\uddf6\ud835\uddf9\ud835\uddf9\ud835\ude00 & \ud835\udde7\ud835\uddfc\ud835\uddfc\ud835\uddf9\ud835\ude00: Python, Kubernetes, Ansible, SaltStack, Prometheus, CI/CD-pipelines & Linux.\n\nHere are a few examples of my work:\n\n\u2022 Product Owner of Secure Dropzone, a secure file transfers application with over 25k of transfers in the last year. Currently working on getting the newer version with end-to-end encryption to market and migrating the SaaS version to a Kubernetes platform.\n\n\u2022 Responsible for becoming compliant with security standards. This includes the KPN Security Policy (KSP), CIS Benchmarks any many more. Created a framework for automating the auditing and reporting using Ansible.\n\n\u2022 Developed custom Ansible modules, plug-ins and REST API clients using Python. The modules allow others to automate both network components and closed source applications.\n\n\u2022 Made several\u00a0contributions to open source, to tools such as SaltStack, Prometheus, rfcat and many more.\n\nI get excited about opportunities where I'm able to work with skilled engineers to develop secure and automated cloud platforms.\n\nLet's connect and discuss how I can contribute to your team's success. Reach out at roald.nefs@warpnet.nl or send me a message here on LinkedIn.",
